                        Hurley
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d319</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">319</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-09-18T05:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-09-18T05:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-18T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-18T05:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-18T17:00:00+07:00">September 18, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 18—4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1612. Favorable developments in Government-Communist negotiations indicated.
                    Slight delay in my departure might be helpful in situation.</p>
                <pb facs="0476" n="466" xml:id="pg_466"/>
                <p>Accordingly General Wedemeyer is proceeding to Washington, leaving Shanghai
                    September 19. My plans are now to leave here on plane already scheduled to
                    depart Saturday, September 23.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
